{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d49f-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s798A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"798A"},"text":"§ 798A.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Temporary extension of section 794","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s794"},"text":"section 794 of this title","children":[],"tail":", as amended and extended by section 1(a)(29) of the Emergency Powers Continuation Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/333"},"text":"66 Stat. 333","children":[],"tail":"), as further amended by Public Law 12, Eighty-third Congress, in addition to coming into full force and effect in time of war shall remain in full force and effect until six months after the termination of the national emergency proclaimed by the President on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-12-16"},"text":"December 16, 1950","children":[],"tail":" (Proc. 2912, 3 C.F.R., 1950 Supp., p. 71), or such earlier date as may be prescribed by concurrent resolution of the Congress, and acts which would give rise to legal consequences and penalties under section 794 when performed during a state of war shall give rise to the same legal consequences and penalties when they are performed during the period above provided for."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8e0d4a0-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1953-06-30/ch175/s4"},"text":"June 30, 1953, ch. 175, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/67/133"},"text":"67 Stat. 133","children":[],"tail":", § 798; renumbered § 798A, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647/tXXXV/s3519/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647, title XXXV, § 3519(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4923"},"text":"104 Stat. 4923","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8e0d4a1-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8e0d4a2-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb8e0d4a3-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 1(a)(29) of the Emergency Powers Continuation Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/333"},"text":"66 Stat. 333","children":[],"tail":") as further amended by Public Law 12, Eighty-third Congress, referred to in text, was formerly set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s791"},"text":"section 791 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and was repealed by section 7 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1953-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1953","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Proc. 2912, 3 C.F.R., 1950 Supp., p. 71, referred to in text, probably should refer to Proc. 2914, which is set out as a note preceding ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1"},"text":"section 1 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8e344a4-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/647"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–647","children":[],"tail":" renumbered the second "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s798"},"text":"section 798 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb8e344a5-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idb8e344a6-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of National Emergency","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Declaration of national emergency in effect on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-09-14"},"text":"Sept. 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", was terminated two years from that date by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1601"},"text":"section 1601 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
